lead_paragraph: Right to Rise has raised more than $100 million to help Mr. Bush secure the Republican nomination. Critics say it has little to show for it.

byline.original: By ASHLEY PARKER and MAGGIE HABERMAN

headline.print_headline: As Bush’s Bid Lags, Some Blame ‘Super PAC’ That Raised $100 Million
headline.main: As Jeb Bush Struggles, Some Allies Blame His ‘Super PAC’

snippet: Right to Rise has raised more than $100 million to help Mr. Bush secure the Republican nomination. Critics say it has little to show for it.
abstract: Financial backers of Jeb Bush's presidential campaign have begun criticizing super PAC Right to Rise, which raised over $100 million for Bush in 2015, for its inability to have impact on his low standings; frustrations are on display at private meeting between group's chief strategist Mike Murphy and financial backers in Manhattan.
